cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is about word alignment, which is a task in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes an unsupervised learning approach using log-linear models, which is a common technique in machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also introduces a contrastive approach, which is a technique commonly used in statistics and information theory, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
